  "prompt": "What are the negative affects of ZMA (Zinc Monomethionine Aspartate)?",
  "response": "While ZMA (Zinc Monomethionine Aspartate) is generally considered safe when taken as directed, there are potential negative effects and considerations:\n\n1. Potential Side Effects:\n- Nausea\n- Stomach upset\n- Diarrhea\n- Potential interactions with certain medications\n\n2. Mineral Interactions:\n- High zinc intake can interfere with copper and iron absorption\n- May reduce absorption of other minerals if taken in excess\n\n3. Overdose Risks:\n- Excessive zinc can cause:\n- Immune system suppression\n- Copper deficiency\n- Reduced HDL cholesterol levels\n- Impaired immune function\n\n4. Potential Sleep Disruption:\n- Some users report sleep disturbances\n- Possible vivid dreams or nightmares\n\n5. Hormonal Considerations:\n- May slightly impact testosterone levels\n- Potential interactions with hormone-related conditions\n\n6. Allergic Reactions:\n- Rare instances of allergic responses\n- Potential skin rashes or respiratory issues\n\n7. Contraindications:\n- Not recommended for individuals with certain medical conditions\n- Should consult healthcare professional before use\n\nAlways follow recommended dosages and consult a healthcare professional before starting any supplement regimen.",
